                <head>456. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>Portuguese Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_SAO1">Antonio de Oliveira
                        Salazar</persName> underwent emergency brain surgery on September 6, 1968,
                    and slipped into a coma <pb facs="0835" n="787" xml:id="pg_787"/> on September
                    16. On September 26, President Americo de Deus Rodrigues Tomas announced that
                    Salazar would not recover and appointed Marcello Caetano as his successor.
                    Secretary <persName corresp="#p_RD3">Rusk</persName> visited Lisbon November
                    18–19 and met with Prime Minister Caetano and Foreign Minister <persName
                        corresp="#p_NF1">Nogueira</persName>. Memoranda of conversation recording
                    the Secretary’s discussions with Caetano and <persName corresp="#p_NF1"
                        >Nogueira</persName> are in Department of State, Central Files, ORG 7 S.
                    Three of these memoranda are scheduled for publication in <ref
                        target="frus1964-68v12">
                        <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1964–1968, volume XII</ref>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
